    abstract = {Adoption of life science knowledge bases by domain experts remains low in spite of the increasing accessibility of these bases, as the Semantic Web framework supports advanced integration and querying. The main bottleneck for leveraging these knowledge bases is that advanced querying combines the inner complexity of life sciences (which requires domain expertise) with the technical complexity of knowledge bases schemas and of SPARQL (which requires engineering skills).},
